OL,3,CDrought formally declared in Sussex
OL,5,FThe Environment Agency has officially
OL,6,Fannounced a drought in areas of Sussex
OL,7,Fserved by South East Water, citing low
OL,8,Freservoir levels in the Ardingly
OL,9,FReservoir.
OL,11,FAreas around Haywards Heath and
OL,12,FEastbourne move to drought status,
OL,13,Fwhile adjoining parts of Sussex,
OL,14,FSurrey and Hampshire remain in a
OL,15,Fprolonged dry-weather stage.
OL,17,FThe reservoir's water level is falling
OL,18,Fsharply. Now at just 27.6 % of
OL,19,Fcapacity, after weeks of low rainfall
OL,20,Fand sustained high demand.
